My wife is a photographer and A.I. makes her job faster with the added potential to make her job redundant.  I can tell you that the pictures of all her clients now have the same sky (see first paragraph).

@Justin

Give it a few years. What you're describing is its current limitations. Of course, a machine intelligence that's better at evoking (and potentially manipulating) human emotion than any human has obvious risks, both as a tool for organizations and individuals seeking to gain control over others, and as a feedback loop with dangerous consequences.

Basically we've disconnected fire again, and it's probably going to burn some folks, but it promises to be useful enough to take the risk.

