@SP

It's true that they can analyze vast databases, but the conclusions they come to from their analyses are often just plain wrong. I'm thinking mostly of Google's irritating AI that appears unbidden and unwanted at the top of the search results. So many of its conclusions are just wrong, which I discover when following the links it has supposedly used to create its answers. But even ChatGPT gets it wrong sometimes. Any crossword puzzle created by AI would necessarily need human analysis to ensure the clues and answers are correct.

Whether or not we should use AI is a philosophical/moral issue that I don't have the energy to contemplate right now. But as to your specific artistic case, that strikes me as fine. You yourself are coming up with the specific subject matter and directing the AI. And then you are doing the painting yourself. Finally, you reveal that you were assisted by AI. I have no problem with any of this.

@SP

You are using AI for suggestions, then working them over into your own creation. I don't have a problem with that.

My beef is that AI results are often accepted as fact, truth gospel. AI should never be given the final say.

